{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RYmMrtU6ikhhXW8P2cFL9x","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: add-endpoint\n     3→description: Add a new REST API endpoint with view, URL route, schema, and test. Use when adding endpoints, routes, or API paths.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Add Endpoint\n     7→\n     8→Add a complete API endpoint: view function, URL route, response schema, and test.\n     9→\n    10→## Usage\n    11→\n    12→```bash\n    13→jig run ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/recipe.yaml --vars '{\"view_name\": \"<name>\", \"url_path\": \"<path>\", \"url_name\": \"<name>\", \"schema_name\": \"<Schema>\", \"model_name\": \"<Model>\"}'\n    14→```\n    15→\n    16→If invoked as `/add-endpoint <view_name> <model_name>`:\n    17→\n    18→```bash\n    19→jig run ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/recipe.yaml --vars '{\"view_name\": \"$1\", \"url_path\": \"<inferred>\", \"url_name\": \"<inferred>\", \"schema_name\": \"<inferred>\", \"model_name\": \"$2\"}'\n    20→```\n    21→\n    22→## Variables\n    23→\n    24→- **view_name**: View function name (e.g. `reservation_receipt`)\n    25→- **url_path**: URL path segment (e.g. `reservations/<int:pk>/receipt/`)\n    26→- **url_name**: URL name for reverse lookup (e.g. `reservation-receipt`)\n    27→- **schema_name**: Response schema class name (e.g. `ReceiptSchema`)\n    28→- **model_name**: Django model to query (e.g. `Reservation`)\n    29→\n    30→Extract these from the user's request. Infer url_path and url_name from view_name if not explicit.\n    31→\n    32→## Gotchas\n    33→\n    34→- If jig exits non-zero, it prints the rendered templates to stderr. Use that output to apply changes manually.\n    35→- Run `jig vars ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/recipe.yaml` to confirm required variables if unsure.\n    36→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5bbdd4f0-a7c5-4fb0-9568-d4e9d48f13db","uuid":"7f7b05b4-862c-413c-8408-f62f31d6aa22"}
